summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Three Hundred ($300.00) Dollars out of the general fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of Peter Campbell and Annie Campbell, his wife, for personal injuries received by her on the 19th day of November, 1914, between the hours of ten and eleven o' clock A.M. while traveling on the east side of 11th Avenue Northeast just north of the intersection of 11th Avenue Northeast and Northlake Avenue, in said city, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
